parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Airbag Seat Occupancy Sensor Mat Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger airbag seat occupancy sensor mat can cause the passenger airbag to not deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the passenger airbag off light illuminates
the sensor mat becomes damaged over time
and the airbag does not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum pump can cause the power assist braking function to fail, leading to increased stopping distance and increased risk of a crash.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard to press
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or has reduced braking ability.
